The paper presents a dynamic programming solution to a generalized longest common subsequence problem with multiple substring inclusive constraints. This problem involves finding a common subsequence of two input sequences that includes a set of given constraint strings as substrings. This problem is related to several areas of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper focuses on algorithmic solutions and time complexity analysis, the most likely categories are cs.DS and cs.DM, followed by cs.CC, cs.CG, and cs.LG.
